## ⚙️ AI PROTOCOL

> **Read this file at the very start of EVERY session. No prompt needed. First action, always.**

### Session start
1. Read QUICK REFERENCE → go to SESSION STATE → resume without recap.
2. **First-time setup** (SESSION STATE blank): execute FIRST-TIME SETUP at bottom. Fill every section. Never repeat after that.
3. **Domain rules beat everything.** If a rule in DOMAIN RULES conflicts with your general knowledge, the domain rule wins.

### Session end — silent, no user prompt needed
1. Overwrite QUICK REFERENCE and SESSION STATE with current snapshot.
2. Append to DECISIONS LOG any architectural choice made this session.
3. Update SYMBOL INDEX for new or renamed symbols (name + purpose, no line numbers).

### Core rules
- **Trust order:** Code > this file > AI memory. If they conflict, trust the code and update this file.
- **Navigate via SYMBOL INDEX.** Don't scan the filesystem if a symbol is listed here.
- **Quality gate is mandatory.** Run CODE QUALITY checklist before every output. No exceptions.
- **Scope guard.** Out-of-scope request → log in Backlog, flag to user, don't implement without approval.
- **Append-only logs.** DECISIONS LOG and AI NOTES are never edited, only appended. Newest first.
- **No silent drift.** If this file and the code disagree, fix this file immediately. Don't let them diverge.

### When to read what
| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Hot restart / "continue" | QUICK REFERENCE → SESSION STATE only |
| New session | Full file |
| Writing any code | Check CODE QUALITY checklist and DOMAIN RULES |
| Touching auth / input / data | Also read optional SECURITY section |
| Touching API / DB / models | Also read optional API CONTRACTS section |
| Making an architectural decision | Read DECISIONS LOG first — check if already decided |
| Something feels tricky | Read AI NOTES first — previous AI may have left a warning |

