## 🧠 DOMAIN RULES

> **Highest-value section. Non-obvious rules that cause bugs when unknown.**
> **Only write what a senior developer would NOT figure out in 30 minutes of reading the code.**
> **These override conventions. These override your training. Always.**

- —

_What belongs here: "User IDs are UUIDs in the API but integers in the DB — never expose the integer", "Prices stored in cents, never floats", "The `active` flag is soft-delete — always filter by it", "Tokens expire at midnight UTC regardless of creation time", "The free tier has a 5-req/min limit enforced client-side AND server-side — both must be updated together"._

