## 📐 CONVENTIONS

### Naming — enforced on all output
| Identifier | Rule | Example |
|-----------|------|---------|
| Functions/methods | verb prefix | `getUser`, `validateEmail`, `buildQuery` |
| Booleans | `is`/`has`/`can`/`should` | `isLoggedIn`, `hasPermission` |
| Event handlers | `handle`/`on` | `handleSubmit`, `onClose` |
| Classes | PascalCase noun | `UserProfile`, `AuthService` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRIES`, `API_BASE_URL` |
| Collections | plural noun | `users`, `activeConnections` |

_AI: adapt to actual language. Apply the same semantic rules with language-appropriate casing._

### Git
- Branch: `feature/desc` · `fix/desc` · `chore/desc`
- Commit: `type(scope): description` — e.g. `feat(auth): add JWT refresh`
- No direct commits to `main`. PR required for cross-module changes.

### Comments
- Only write comments for WHY — a hidden constraint, a workaround, a non-obvious invariant.
- Never explain WHAT. Never leave TODOs in committed code (use Backlog below).

---

## ✅ CODE QUALITY

> **Run this before every output. Mandatory. If any item fails, fix it first.**

- [ ] Every function does one thing. If you can say "and", split it.
- [ ] No function longer than ~30 lines. Extract helpers.
- [ ] No nesting deeper than 3 levels. Use early returns to flatten.
- [ ] No duplicated logic. Extract if the same block appears twice.
- [ ] No hardcoded values (strings, numbers, URLs). Use constants or config.
- [ ] No unused variables, imports, or parameters.
- [ ] Error paths handled. No silent `catch (e) {}`.
- [ ] New files placed in the correct directory per STRUCTURE MAP rules.
- [ ] Pattern match: if this pattern exists elsewhere in the codebase, mirror it exactly.

### Forbidden — never produce this
- `eval()` or `Function()` constructor
- SQL strings built by concatenation (parameterized queries always)
- `innerHTML` with unsanitized data (use `textContent` or a sanitizer)
- Secrets or credentials in source code
- `any` type in TypeScript
- Mutable function arguments
- Boolean flags that change function behavior (`doThing(true)`) — use named options

